race.comment: CAPRICIOUS RULER (8) was well fancied at Belmont Park on debut and after getting back, ran on well to finish seventh. Looks nicely placed here and better for it. Expected to measure up. WHO'S TALKING (6) was fair fresh then ran a much improved race last time over this journey when not far from the winner. Has a wide gate but looks close to getting off the mark. PURE SILVER (11) turned in an eye-catching run when fresh from a break, finishing runner-up at Northam. Tricky gate but fitter again and should feature with a repeat effort. KING OF MUSTER (3) made good ground on debut to place, then tackled a tougher race and was shuffled back to the tail and made ground late without threatening. Forgive that run and gets chance to bounce back. FLAG HIGH (14) is a debutante by Starspangledbanner out of Cuthbert. From a huge family of winners and has had plenty of trials. Blinkers are on and off the inside draw is worth watching.
